这是美国海岸巡逻队
this is the United States Coast Guard.

21
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:22,360
停船，准备登船受检
Heave to and prepare to be boarded.

22
00:03:22,610 --> 00:03:25,910
（巫师号）

23
00:03:36,090 --> 00:03:37,240
巫师号
Enchanter,

24
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:40,670
你们挂美国船旗，我们要上船检查
you are a US flag ship and we are going to board you.

25
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:42,550
立刻停航
Heave to now.

26
00:03:54,270 --> 00:03:57,110
请船员到船头集合
Muster your crew on the bow.

27
00:04:08,410 --> 00:04:10,240
好了，站在那里
Okay, hold it there.

28
00:04:13,410 --> 00:04:15,330
你们两个，往前走！
You two, report.

29
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:18,630
兰戴尔，跟我来
Randall, come with me.

30
00:04:24,090 --> 00:04:25,760
别动

31
00:04:26,140 --> 00:04:27,300
跪下！
Kneel down!

32
00:04:30,930 --> 00:04:32,140
船长
Captain.

33
00:04:33,140 --> 00:04:34,440
船长？
Captain?

34
00:04:35,650 --> 00:04:37,270
请说，队长
Go ahead, Senior Chief.

35
00:04:37,940 --> 00:04:39,980
情况不妙
It's a bad one.

36
00:04:40,110 --> 00:04:43,110
赶快派人拿录影机来
I think you better send over the video camera.

37
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:58,500
（中情局总部，维吉尼亚州，兰利市）

38
00:05:00,670 --> 00:05:02,510
杰克，进来吧
Jack, come on in.

39
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:07,500
你桌上的案件堆多高了？
How high is the pile on your desk?

40
00:05:08,060 --> 00:05:08,930
差不多这么高
About this high.

41
00:05:09,010 --> 00:05:10,260
现在更高了
Now it's this high.

42
00:05:10,350 --> 00:05:11,470
又有什么案子？
What have you got?

43
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:13,600
听说南加勒比海的事了吗？
You heard about that business in the south Caribbean?

44
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:14,730
听说了
Yeah, a little bit.

45
00:05:14,810 --> 00:05:16,690
我要全部的细节
I need the full skinny.

46
00:05:16,810 --> 00:05:17,510
什么时候？
By when?

47
00:05:17,610 --> 00:05:18,600
尽快
As soon as you can.

48
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:21,480
好吧
Okay.

49
00:05:21,570 --> 00:05:23,070
- 杰克 - 什么事，长官？
- Jack. - Yes, sir.

50
00:05:23,150 --> 00:05:24,320
要谨慎一点
Be discreet.

51
00:05:25,860 --> 00:05:27,200
什么意思？
What do you mean?

52
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:29,740
你会明白的
You'll find out.

53
00:05:31,660 --> 00:05:33,040
真神秘
Mysterious.

54
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,710
我最爱神秘
I love a mystery.

55
00:05:42,210 --> 00:05:43,630
杰克·莱恩
Ryan, John P.

56
00:05:43,710 --> 00:05:45,380
让他通过
Let him through.

57
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:49,680
- 给你  - 谢谢
- Here you go. - Thank you.

58
00:05:50,390 --> 00:05:51,800
知道怎么走吧？
You know where you're going?

59
00:05:51,860 --> 00:05:53,430
知道，谢谢
Yup. Thank you.

60
00:05:54,100 --> 00:05:56,270
车要停哪里？
Oh, where do I park?

61
00:05:56,350 --> 00:05:58,270
那里
Right over there.

62
00:05:58,350 --> 00:05:59,730
谢谢
Thank you.

63
00:06:09,530 --> 00:06:10,990
我在通道上，正往前走
Okay, I'm in the passageway, going forward.

64
00:06:11,070 --> 00:06:13,200
- 小心台阶  - 经过主人舱房
- Watch your step. - Master stateroom.

65
00:06:13,280 --> 00:06:14,830
甲板上有血渍
Got blood on the deck, blood on the sheets and below.

66
00:06:14,910 --> 00:06:17,500
发现19颗子弹
Nineteen cartridges were recovered...

67
00:06:17,580 --> 00:06:18,660
在下面的地上
Down there, sir. On the ground.

68
00:06:18,850 --> 00:06:20,240
还有…
as well as the...

69
00:06:20,460 --> 00:06:23,040
两支作案用的凶枪
As the two weapons that fired them.

70
00:06:23,130 --> 00:06:24,460
我在甲板下
I'm below deck now...

71
00:06:24,550 --> 00:06:27,480
血液采样跟船主一家人…
Blood samples taken consistent with...

72
00:06:28,520 --> 00:06:29,260
吻合
the crew,

73
00:06:29,380 --> 00:06:31,280
包括哈丁及其妻子
Hardin and his wife,

74
00:06:31,550 --> 00:06:34,470
还有一对儿女
and his son and daughter.

75
00:06:36,890 --> 00:06:39,690
我的床单和枕头上都有血
I got blood on both the sheets and pillow

76
00:06:39,770 --> 00:06:41,000
在右舷和左舷…
on both starboard and portside racks...

77
00:06:41,060 --> 00:06:42,040
（美国海岸巡逻队）

78
00:06:42,150 --> 00:06:44,320
镜子上也有血渍
and there's some blood up there on the mirror, too.

79
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:46,730
他们是在主人舱房遇害的
They were killed in their staterooms,

80
00:06:46,820 --> 00:06:49,400
显然当时在睡觉
apparently as they slept,

81
00:06:49,490 --> 00:06:52,110
然后被拖到上层甲板，再扔到海里
dragged topside and thrown overboard.

82
00:06:53,810 --> 00:06:55,900
两名束手就擒的嫌犯
The two men in custody surrendered

83
00:06:55,970 --> 00:06:58,450
曾企图躲避巡逻队的缉捕
after a brief attempt to outrun the Coast Guard.

84
00:06:58,580 --> 00:07:01,920
我们对嫌犯了解多少？
What do we know about them, the men in custody?

85
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:08,420
在波哥大因多次贩毒而被捕，总统先生
Half a dozen arrests for drug trafficking in Bogota, Mr. President.

86
00:07:09,590 --> 00:07:10,800
贩毒…
Drugs.

87
00:07:12,970 --> 00:07:14,050
怀疑和卡里的犯罪集团有关
Suspected ties to the Cali cartel

88
00:07:15,430 --> 00:07:16,430
而不是梅德林…
not Medellin...

89
00:07:16,510 --> 00:07:17,810
你还好吗，詹姆斯？
You all right, James?

90
00:07:17,930 --> 00:07:19,430
根据缉毒署的资料
according to DEA.

91
00:07:20,350 --> 00:07:21,640
为什么？
Why?

92
00:07:21,770 --> 00:07:25,020
没什么，总统，只是杀人抢劫嘛
Nothing exotic, sir. Straight piracy and murder.

93
00:07:25,110 --> 00:07:26,820
这又不是头一遭
It's not the first time.

94
00:07:28,650 --> 00:07:31,650
这可是头一遭我的好友遇害
It's the first time it was a friend of mine.

95
00:07:33,700 --> 00:07:34,990
是的，总统
Yes, sir.

96
00:07:42,160 --> 00:07:43,790
你刚刚怎么了？没事吧？
What was that in there? Are you all right?

97
00:07:43,870 --> 00:07:45,040
没事
Yeah.

98
00:07:45,790 --> 00:07:48,380
老天，我36小时没睡了，刚才有讲清楚吗？
Geez, I haven't slept in 36 hours. I make any sense?

99
00:07:48,460 --> 00:07:50,550
不知道耶，你刚讲了什么？
I don't know. What did you say?

100
00:07:50,630 --> 00:07:52,380
开玩笑的，讲得很好
Just kidding. Good job.

101
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:58,010
你该上上交际课，巴比
You ought to give diplomacy lessons, Bobby.

102
00:07:58,140 --> 00:07:59,770
我只是照实说 这是我的职责
I call it the way I see it. That's my job.

103
00:07:59,850 --> 00:08:01,230
詹姆斯！
James.

104
00:08:01,310 --> 00:08:02,350
他找你
And he's yours.

105
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:03,850
等我一下
Wait for me.

106
00:08:08,820 --> 00:08:10,320
把门关上
Shut the door.

107
00:08:14,200 --> 00:08:15,450
我向美国人民保证过
I promised the American people

108
00:08:15,530 --> 00:08:19,240
要扼止毒品入侵这国家
I would do something about the drugs pouring into this country.

109
00:08:19,330 --> 00:08:20,540
你有啊
You are.

110
00:08:21,660 --> 00:08:22,910
我们协助哥伦比亚
We support the Colombians' efforts

111
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:25,710
对抗毒贩，提供设备而且…
against the cartels with equipment and...

112
00:08:25,830 --> 00:08:27,710
而且一无所获！
And accomplish nothing.

113
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,250
这些毒贩怎么想？
What do these drug dealers think?

114
00:08:30,340 --> 00:08:31,590
以为我们无能吗？是这样吗？
We're powerless, is that what they think?

115
00:08:31,670 --> 00:08:33,920
他们自以为能为所欲为
They think they can keep doing this kind of thing

116
00:08:34,010 --> 00:08:36,260
永远不受制裁！
and there's no response, ever.

117
00:08:38,760 --> 00:08:41,270
你提议采取行动吗，总统？
Are you suggesting a course of action, sir?

118
00:08:42,270 --> 00:08:44,830
我想提议的…
The course of action I'd suggest...

119
00:08:45,370 --> 00:08:47,520
是我不能提议的
is a course of action I can't suggest.

120
00:09:02,700 --> 00:09:03,900
这样我…
I'm...

121
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:06,250
不确定该怎么做
not sure where that leaves us.

122
00:09:10,540 --> 00:09:14,340
贩毒集团对美国国家安全
These drug cartels represent a clear and present danger

123
00:09:14,420 --> 00:09:17,550
是迫切的危机
to the national security of the United States.

124
00:09:25,230 --> 00:09:30,230
（哥伦比亚，卡里市，埃内斯托·埃斯科贝多庄园）

125
00:09:53,300 --> 00:09:55,050
柯特斯！柯特斯！
Cortez! Cortez!

126
00:10:07,980 --> 00:10:09,940
知道你干了什么好事吗？
Do you know what you've done?

127
00:10:10,850 --> 00:10:12,270
我杀了一个小偷
I killed a thief

128
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:15,190
我杀了一个偷我钱的…
a thief who was stealing

129
00:10:17,650 --> 00:10:18,700
…臭小偷！
from me!

130
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:23,280
还有他太太、儿子、女儿
And his wife, and his son, and his daughter.

131
00:10:23,370 --> 00:10:25,950
显然根本没顾虑到后果
Apparently with no thought of the consequences

132
00:10:29,210 --> 00:10:30,580
哦，我好想等他的孩子长大
Oh, I want his kids to grow up

133
00:10:30,670 --> 00:10:32,420
趁我没预料到时
and avenge their father's death

134
00:10:32,500 --> 00:10:34,300
替他父亲报仇…
when I least expect it...

135
00:10:35,130 --> 00:10:36,630
他是美国总统的
He was a good friend

136
00:10:37,050 --> 00:10:38,470
好朋友
and political ally of the

137
00:10:38,550 --> 00:10:40,800
兼政治伙伴
President of the United States

138
00:10:49,640 --> 00:10:51,690
我不感到意外
That doesn't surprise me.

139
00:10:52,690 --> 00:10:54,730
你至少该担心了
It should at the very least concern you.

140
00:10:54,820 --> 00:10:56,150
他们能拿我怎样？
What are they going to do?

141
00:10:56,230 --> 00:10:58,650
通缉我？逮捕我？
Come after me? Arrest me?

142
00:10:59,740 --> 00:11:01,490
你在吓唬我
You're scaring me.

143
00:11:03,490 --> 00:11:06,430
你能不能停下来好好听我说？
Will you stop long enough for me to tell you something important?

144
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:12,330
谢谢
Thank you.

145
00:11:15,540 --> 00:11:19,470
听好，你请我当顾问
Listen, you pay me to counsel you,

146
00:11:19,550 --> 00:11:21,930
我就该提供你意见
and I am counseling you.

147
00:11:22,010 --> 00:11:24,970
我的情报能让你活命
I'm keeping you alive with information.

148
00:11:25,050 --> 00:11:28,390
如果你不听我
Now, if you disregard my counsel,

149
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:31,640
继续照自己的方式经营生意
if you keep running your business the way you have been

150
00:11:31,730 --> 00:11:34,650
只用子弹，不用脑袋
with your balls instead of your head,

151
00:11:34,730 --> 00:11:36,900
就会有两种结果
two things will happen.

152
00:11:37,020 --> 00:11:39,740
我闪人，你丧命
I'll quit, and you'll get killed.

153
00:11:51,910 --> 00:11:54,630
你忘了跟我报告出差的结果
You forgot to tell me about your scouting trip.

154
00:11:56,090 --> 00:11:57,340
我没忘
No, I didn't.

155
00:11:57,420 --> 00:12:00,420
你又找了一个通风报信的 他是谁？
You made another contact. Who is he?

156
00:12:00,550 --> 00:12:03,630
卡斯特罗也常问我，我的情报来源是谁
Castro always asked me the same question about my sources,

157
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:05,680
我总是给他一样的答案
and I always gave him the same answer.

158
00:12:05,760 --> 00:12:08,760
对，但卡斯特罗付给你的钱没有我多
Yes, but Castro didn't pay you what I pay you.

159
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:11,890
这个人不用花你一毛钱
This one will cost you nothing.

160
00:12:14,310 --> 00:12:15,600
女人
A woman.

161
00:12:16,270 --> 00:12:18,150
你在利用女人
You're using a woman.

162
00:12:25,910 --> 00:12:27,450
浮不起来！
It won't float!

163
00:12:29,740 --> 00:12:31,970
约翰，你要吐司还是…？
John, what do you want, toast or...

164
00:12:32,100 --> 00:12:33,160
松饼
Waffles.

165
00:12:33,250 --> 00:12:34,500
我没时间做松饼
I don't have time for waffles.

166
00:12:34,580 --> 00:12:36,580
- 你只能吃吐司  - 有没有看到我的钥匙？
- You can have toast or toast. - Anybody seen my keys?

167
00:12:36,670 --> 00:12:39,420
不是在大厅桌上，就是在你口袋
They're either on the front hall table or in your pocket.

168
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:40,880
- 约翰  - 煎饼！
- John. - Pancakes!

169
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:42,590
我的钥匙呢？真是的
Now, where are my keys? Shoot.

170
00:12:42,670 --> 00:12:43,880
- 给我吐司  - 谢谢
- Toast, please. - Thank you.

171
00:12:43,970 --> 00:12:45,590
- 拜  - 拜，宝贝
- Bye. - Bye, honey.

172
00:12:45,680 --> 00:12:47,010
- 拜，爸  - 拜，小家伙
- Bye, Dad. - Bye, pal.

173
00:12:47,090 --> 00:12:49,470
- 爸，这不会浮  - 喂？
- Daddy, it won't float. - Hello?

174
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:51,060
- 是的  - 它不应该浮的
- Yes. - It's not supposed to float.

175
00:12:51,140 --> 00:12:53,390
这是潜艇，在水里航行的船
It's a submarine. It's a boat that goes underwater.

176
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:54,940
- 爸  - 杰克
- Dad. - Jack.

177
00:12:58,440 --> 00:12:59,610
喂？
Hello?

178
00:13:02,650 --> 00:13:03,780
什么时候？
When?

179
00:13:03,860 --> 00:13:06,190
（男性杂志，60件事）

180
00:13:06,280 --> 00:13:08,280
本来以为是感冒
I thought I had the flu.

181
00:13:08,950 --> 00:13:12,040
他们要是没告诉我，我还会以为是感冒
I'd still think I had the flu if they weren't telling me otherwise.

182
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:16,000
他们说了什么？
Well, what... What are they telling you?

183
00:13:18,380 --> 00:13:21,550
恶性胰脏癌
Pancreatic cancer of an aggressive nature,

184
00:13:21,630 --> 00:13:22,880
没听错的话
if I heard them right.

185
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:24,340
老天
Jesus.

186
00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:27,630
那是什么意思？
Well, what does that mean?

187
00:13:28,470 --> 00:13:31,010
我想意思是我快玩完了
I guess it means I'm in big trouble.

188
00:13:31,680 --> 00:13:34,890
不，我是说可以切除吗？
No, I mean, can they... Can they operate or...

189
00:13:34,980 --> 00:13:35,920
也许吧
Maybe.

190
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:38,190
他们说也许吧
That's what they said. "Maybe."

191
00:13:38,310 --> 00:13:42,020
在我听来应该是不行
But it sounds suspiciously like "no" to me.

192
00:13:42,150 --> 00:13:44,150
他就是他们其中一人
There's one of them now.

193
00:13:46,650 --> 00:13:49,160
嘿，我还没挂掉
Hey, I'm not dead yet.

194
00:13:51,330 --> 00:13:53,620
不过我人在医院
But I am in the hospital,

195
00:13:53,700 --> 00:13:56,620
不在办公室
which means that I'm not in my office,

196
00:13:56,710 --> 00:13:59,290
因此不知道局里的状况
which means I don't know what's going on.

197
00:13:59,370 --> 00:14:00,710
我需要你驻守
I need you there.

198
00:14:01,710 --> 00:14:05,050
- 哪里？  - 我的办公室，代替我的职务
- Where? - In my office, doing my job.

199
00:14:05,170 --> 00:14:06,130
慢点，我…
No, wait. I...

200
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:09,640
我最讨厌在状况外，杰克，这点你知道
I hate not knowing what's going on, Jack. You know that.

201
00:14:09,720 --> 00:14:12,680
我怕我不能胜任你的工作
I wouldn't know the first thing about doing your job, sir.

202
00:14:12,760 --> 00:14:15,810
你一直都有参与，我们没秘密
You've been around. No big mystery.

203
00:14:15,890 --> 00:14:17,350
你也去过白宫
You've been to the White House.

204
00:14:17,430 --> 00:14:19,520
一次而已，而且我不喜欢
Once. I hated it.

205
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:21,190
不，才不是
No, you didn't.

206
00:14:22,270 --> 00:14:24,650
想知道华府的政治哲学吗？
Want to know about politics in Washington?

207
00:14:24,730 --> 00:14:26,360
四个字
Four words.

208
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:28,450
“小心为上”杰克
Watch your back, Jack.

209
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:35,240
巴比？
Bobby?

210
00:14:35,370 --> 00:14:36,920
你应该要第一个知道
You should be the first to know,

211
00:14:37,020 --> 00:14:39,710
也许是第三或第四个知道
or I guess the third or fourth to know.

212
00:14:39,790 --> 00:14:43,290
我指派莱恩为情报局代理副局长
I'm appointing Ryan the Acting Deputy Director, Intelligence.

213
00:14:43,380 --> 00:14:45,770
当然这是暂时的
Now, it'll be a provisional appointment, of course,

214
00:14:45,840 --> 00:14:47,880
直到詹姆斯康复为止
until James recovers.

215
00:14:48,970 --> 00:14:50,200
我要你尽快跟他说明
I want you to get him up to speed

216
00:14:50,270 --> 00:14:52,680
我们对哥伦比亚的资助计划
on our aid program to the Colombians.

217
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:54,760
他要跟监督委员会报告
He's got to brief the oversight committee

218
00:14:54,890 --> 00:14:57,560
说服他们再拨七千五百万的预算
and talk them out of another $75 million.

219
00:14:57,640 --> 00:15:00,560
而且不能让他像个大傻瓜
And not make a complete fool out of himself.

220
00:15:03,270 --> 00:15:05,440
哈丁家族谋杀案进行得如何？
What's happening on the Hardin murders?

221
00:15:05,570 --> 00:15:06,530
我在处理中
I'm on it.

222
00:15:06,610 --> 00:15:09,240
总统要求彻底调查
The President's calling for a full-court press.

223
00:15:09,320 --> 00:15:13,910
那么你们俩要密切配合了
So, you guys are going to be working together, hand in hand.

224
00:15:15,740 --> 00:15:17,240
太好了
That's great.

225
00:15:32,930 --> 00:15:34,260
玛格丽特
Margaret.

226
00:15:35,430 --> 00:15:36,930
他的东西留着吧
Why don't we leave all his things?

227
00:15:37,080 --> 00:15:38,310
好的
Okay.

228
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:52,600
莱恩
Ryan.

229
00:15:52,930 --> 00:15:54,280
令人难以置信！
I can't believe it!

230
00:15:54,360 --> 00:15:56,370
你是指他不上道吗？
He's not a team player, is that what you're saying?

231
00:15:56,450 --> 00:15:58,240
不只不上道
Not a team player?

232
00:15:58,330 --> 00:15:59,950
还是个童子军
He's a Boy Scout.

233
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:03,460
该死的童子军
He's a goddamn Boy Scout.

234
00:16:03,540 --> 00:16:06,920
相信忠诚、无私，还喜欢打童军绳
Believes in loyalty, cleanliness and knot tying.

235
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:09,050
那就把他排除在外
So leave him out of it.

236
00:16:09,130 --> 00:16:11,550
他可是情报局副局长，詹姆斯
He's the Deputy Director of Intelligence, James.

237
00:16:11,630 --> 00:16:13,340
这下有点麻烦了，你不觉得吗？
It's going to be a little tricky, don't you think?

238
00:16:13,470 --> 00:16:15,930
怎么会？他需要知道什么？
Why? What does he need to know?

239
00:16:16,010 --> 00:16:17,550
不需要
Nothing.

240
00:16:17,640 --> 00:16:19,770
他什么都不需要知道
He needs to know nothing.

241
00:16:19,850 --> 00:16:21,980
他也不会知道
He's going to know nothing.

242
00:16:23,310 --> 00:16:25,270
我要一份拷贝，证明总统授权
I want a copy of the President's authorization

243
00:16:25,350 --> 00:16:28,070
对犯罪集团采取新行动
of this new action against the cartels.

244
00:16:29,650 --> 00:16:31,190
你要什么？
You want what?

245
00:16:31,740 --> 00:16:33,320
你听到了
You heard me.

246
00:16:34,700 --> 00:16:36,410
这件事他并不知情
He doesn't know about it.

247
00:16:38,240 --> 00:16:40,700
让我跟你解释清楚
Let me explain it to you very simply.

248
00:16:40,830 --> 00:16:43,830
这是你答应的，不是我
This is your deal, not mine.

249
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:47,500
除非我有授权书
So unless I have written authorization,

250
00:16:47,570 --> 00:16:49,540
否则你没戏唱
this thing is over before it begins

251
00:16:49,710 --> 00:16:51,760
因为我可不想在东窗事发时
because I'm not going to be the only one left

252
00:16:51,840 --> 00:16:54,420
成为代罪羔羊
without a chair when the music stops.

253
00:17:10,440 --> 00:17:12,230
（发文者：国家安全顾问）

254
00:17:16,700 --> 00:17:20,780
（总统授权中情局副局长，罗伯特·里特）

255
00:17:20,950 --> 00:17:23,410
（负责执行互惠行动包含…）

256
00:17:26,540 --> 00:17:29,250
（目的：执行对抗卡里犯罪集团的准军事行动）

257
00:17:29,420 --> 00:17:31,590
（詹姆斯·卡特）

258
00:17:33,090 --> 00:17:35,380
（巴拿马，巴拿马市）

259
00:17:35,420 --> 00:17:36,720
互惠行动
"Reciprocity."

260
00:17:36,970 --> 00:17:38,720
真聪明的名字
That's a clever name for it.

261
00:17:39,140 --> 00:17:43,390
复仇可是非常、非常危险的动机
Revenge is a very, very, very dangerous motivation.

262
00:17:45,430 --> 00:17:47,690
你到底能不能负责执行这个行动？
Are you able to handle this operation or not?

263
00:17:47,770 --> 00:17:51,400
我要的只是简单的能或不能
What I'm looking for here is a simple yes or no.

264
00:17:51,480 --> 00:17:54,610
你要的是一场政治混乱
What you're looking for is a political mess.

265
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:56,030
- 能或不能？  - 这是他们要的吗？
- Yes or no? - Is that what they want?

266
00:17:56,110 --> 00:17:57,530
因为这可要付出代价的
Because that's what this is.

267
00:17:57,610 --> 00:18:00,490
第一任政府的人要的
They want what every first-term administration wants.

268
00:18:00,570 --> 00:18:02,080
都是连任
A second term.

269
00:18:03,620 --> 00:18:07,000
我想国会山庄的人不会同意的
I don't imagine the boys on the Hill have approved this.

270
00:18:12,630 --> 00:18:13,960
对吧？
Have they?

271
00:18:16,630 --> 00:18:18,260
你意思是不？
Is that a no?

272
00:18:24,470 --> 00:18:25,640
可恶
Shit.

273
00:18:27,100 --> 00:18:30,980
我要你立刻把钱汇到我的户头
I want the money in my account before I move an inch.

274
00:18:32,940 --> 00:18:34,190
没问题
You got it.

275
00:18:34,270 --> 00:18:36,400
- 我要一组卫星通讯  - 没问题
- I'll need a Comsat link. - You got it.

276
00:18:36,490 --> 00:18:37,690
一支突击队
An insertion team.

277
00:18:37,780 --> 00:18:40,700
- 你可以有一整支部队  - 我不要一整支部队
- You can have a brigade. - I don't want a frigging brigade.

278
00:18:40,780 --> 00:18:43,660
我只要12名会打游击战的士兵
I just need 12 men who understand discretionary warfare.

279
00:18:43,780 --> 00:18:46,120
特种部队，会说西班牙文
Special Ops people, Spanish speaking.

280
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:47,830
卡特会找到士兵
Cutter will get the military.

281
00:18:49,370 --> 00:18:52,290
（华盛顿，杜勒斯机场）

282
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:56,800
- 你好吗，先生？  - 很好
- How are you today, sir? - Very well.

283
00:18:56,880 --> 00:18:59,670
- 此行的目的是什么？  - 做生意
- And what is the purpose of your visit? - Business.

284
00:19:00,510 --> 00:19:02,470
做什么生意？
What kind of business are you in?

285
00:19:02,550 --> 00:19:03,710
我卖牵引机
I sell tractors.

286
00:19:03,790 --> 00:19:05,810
我生产并销售牵引机
Well, I build them. Then I sell them.

287
00:19:07,140 --> 00:19:09,270
你要停留多久？
And how long will you be staying?

288
00:19:09,350 --> 00:19:10,980
几天吧
A few days.

289
00:19:11,140 --> 00:19:13,350
（护照身分无误，姓名：兰达、罗伯托-阿隆诺）

290
00:19:38,880 --> 00:19:40,300
当然有风险
Of course it's a risk.

291
00:19:40,380 --> 00:19:42,720
我知道，不过还有什么选择？
I know it's a risk but what's the alternative?

292
00:19:42,840 --> 00:19:45,640
在视网膜做大量放射线治疗吗？
Zapping a retina with 6,000 rads of cobalt?

293
00:19:45,720 --> 00:19:47,430
那可不是闹着玩的
That is not a pretty picture.

294
00:19:47,510 --> 00:19:50,270
总比癌细胞扩散到大脑好
Prettier than a tumor spreading into the cranial sac.

295
00:19:50,350 --> 00:19:52,140
- 已经扩散到眼球了  - 她叫什么名字？
- Enough already about the eyeball. - What is her name?

296
00:19:52,230 --> 00:19:53,850
我在吃午餐
I'm trying to have my lunch.

297
00:19:55,230 --> 00:19:57,480
听好
Listen.

298
00:19:57,570 --> 00:19:59,690
- 你饿了吗？  - 饿死了
- Hungry? - Starved.

299
00:19:59,780 --> 00:20:02,240
因为我们可以省掉午餐
Because we could forget about lunch.

300
00:20:02,360 --> 00:20:04,820
上回就是这样，记得吗？
Oh, we did that last time, remember?

301
00:20:04,910 --> 00:20:07,030
我记得吗？你记得吗？
Do I remember? Do you?

302
00:20:09,580 --> 00:20:11,200
模模糊糊的
Vaguely.

303
00:20:11,290 --> 00:20:13,420
也许我该唤起你的记忆
Maybe I should refresh your memory.

304
00:20:15,880 --> 00:20:16,920
也许吧，打扰一下
Maybe you should.

305
00:20:17,040 --> 00:20:19,000
你的桌位准备好了
Excuse me? Your table is ready now.

306
00:20:19,090 --> 00:20:20,840
让给别人吧，我来叫车
Give it to somebody else. I'll get a cab.

307
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:22,630
莫伊拉？
Moira?

308
00:20:22,720 --> 00:20:24,010
我就知道是你
Oh, I thought that was you.

309
00:20:24,090 --> 00:20:25,390
你好吗？杰克好吗？
How are you? How's Jack?

310
00:20:25,480 --> 00:20:27,890
他很好
He's great, just great.

311
00:20:27,970 --> 00:20:29,300
你还在联邦调查局工作？
You still with the FBI?

312
00:20:29,360 --> 00:20:31,020
是的，替局长工作
Oh, yeah, in the Director's office.

313
00:20:31,100 --> 00:20:32,080
那位是谁？
Who was that?

314
00:20:32,280 --> 00:20:33,400
我的新朋友
My new friend,

315
00:20:33,740 --> 00:20:35,560
罗伯托·兰达
Señor Roberto Landa.

316
00:20:36,810 --> 00:20:38,260
他长得像不像杰克？
Doesn't he look like Jack?

317
00:20:38,490 --> 00:20:39,770
哦，是吗？
Oh, does he?

318
00:20:39,900 --> 00:20:42,610
- 我没看清楚  - 只是拉丁版的
- I can't quite see. - Only Latin.

319
00:20:42,740 --> 00:20:44,060
拉丁版的杰克·莱恩？
A Latin Jack Ryan?

320
00:20:44,170 --> 00:20:46,110
那我非看不可了
Oh, well, this I have to see.

321
00:20:46,780 --> 00:20:48,740
我得走了，拜
I have to go. Bye.

322
00:20:51,160 --> 00:20:53,830
我们知道这不是海盗
Well, we know it's not piracy.

323
00:20:53,910 --> 00:20:55,750
海盗偷船
Pirates steal boats.

324
00:20:56,420 --> 00:20:58,210
（游艇灭门惨案 哈丁全家人惨遭杀害）
这些家伙有迈阿密飞往波哥大的机票
These guys had plane tickets, Miami to Bogota

325
00:20:58,290 --> 00:21:00,840
打算作案后隔天早上潜逃
the morning after the killings.

326
00:21:00,920 --> 00:21:02,550
- 嘿，丹恩  - 情况如何？
- Hey, Dan. - How's it going?

327
00:21:02,630 --> 00:21:04,630
我们在找犯罪动机
Well, we're sneaking up on a motive here.

328
00:21:04,760 --> 00:21:06,020
这位是丹恩·穆雷探员
Dan Murray, Bureau.

329
00:21:06,130 --> 00:21:07,970
拉尔夫·威廉，缉毒署
Ralph Williams, DEA.

330
00:21:08,090 --> 00:21:09,190
有招供吗？
Said anything yet?

331
00:21:09,360 --> 00:21:11,100
有 “我们是无辜的”
Yeah. "We're innocent."

332
00:21:12,270 --> 00:21:13,820
等检查官跟他们提协议吧
Till the DA offers them a deal.

333
00:21:13,910 --> 00:21:14,890
已经提过了
He already has.

334
00:21:14,980 --> 00:21:15,780
普通的
Regular

335
00:21:15,910 --> 00:21:17,400
还是酥脆的
or extra crispy.

336
00:21:17,480 --> 00:21:20,270
他指的是炸鸡，也是电椅
He was either referring to fried chicken or the electric chair.

337
00:21:21,650 --> 00:21:22,980
你认为是什么？
What are you picturing here?

338
00:21:23,110 --> 00:21:26,820
正派的美国商人惨遭灭门？
A hit on a respectable American businessman and his family?

339
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:31,660
假设他是正派
You're assuming he's respectable.

340
00:21:32,120 --> 00:21:33,830
（彼得·哈丁工业）

341
