383
00:23:22,560 --> 00:23:24,510
- 把这个印出来，好吗？  - 好，长官
- Print me up that one, will you? - Yes, sir.

384
00:23:25,730 --> 00:23:26,940
做得好
My boy.

385
00:23:28,110 --> 00:23:31,030
然后三年前，哈丁收到一大笔…
And then three years ago, Hardin received a large infusion

386
00:23:31,110 --> 00:23:32,570
海外投资资金
of foreign investment capital

387
00:23:33,070 --> 00:23:35,870
他用这笔资金大量投资20家购物中心
which he invested wisely in 20 major shopping centers

388
00:23:35,950 --> 00:23:38,040
从沃夫兹堡到亚特兰大都有
from Fort Worth to Atlanta.

389
00:23:38,120 --> 00:23:40,620
我说大量是因为在经济衰退期间
I say "wisely" because in the middle of the recession,

390
00:23:40,750 --> 00:23:44,670
他还能创造可观利润，比起国税局来说
he posted record profits, at least to the IRS,

391
00:23:44,750 --> 00:23:47,590
他显然更怕自己的合伙人
who he apparently feared more than his own partners.

392
00:23:47,670 --> 00:23:48,610
对他们来说
To them,

393
00:23:48,750 --> 00:23:51,630
根据他给股东的报表…
according to the stockholder statements he was giving them,

394
00:23:52,300 --> 00:23:54,770
购物中心的生意不太好
the shopping centers weren't doing nearly as well.

395
00:23:55,210 --> 00:23:56,100
以前是
They were.

396
00:23:56,180 --> 00:23:58,520
他却独吞大笔利润
He was just skimming the lion's share of the profits,

397
00:23:58,580 --> 00:24:00,180
六亿五千万元
$650 million,

398
00:24:00,270 --> 00:24:01,890
分别存在数个银行户头
and putting it in numbered accounts

399
00:24:01,980 --> 00:24:03,770
有些在卢森堡、巴拿马
in Luxembourg, Panama,

400
00:24:04,160 --> 00:24:05,270
有些在开曼群岛
and the Cayman Islands.

401
00:24:06,980 --> 00:24:08,940
他们为了钱杀他
They killed him for it.

402
00:24:09,360 --> 00:24:12,030
- 谁？ - 他的合伙人
- Who? - His partners.

403
00:24:12,530 --> 00:24:14,610
谁是他的合伙人？
Who were his partners?

404
00:24:14,700 --> 00:24:16,990
显然他…
Well, it seems clear that...

405
00:24:17,990 --> 00:24:21,370
他帮哥伦比亚的贩毒集团洗钱
That he was laundering money for the Colombian drug cartels.

406
00:24:21,450 --> 00:24:22,660
老天
Jesus!

407
00:24:24,040 --> 00:24:25,880
我认识这个人四十年了
I knew the man for 40 years.

408
00:24:25,960 --> 00:24:28,090
我们一起读书
We went to school together.

409
00:24:28,170 --> 00:24:30,760
差点一起合伙做生意
We almost went into business together.

410
00:24:30,840 --> 00:24:32,970
那会赚不少钱
That would have been good.

411
00:24:35,180 --> 00:24:38,140
哦，老天，媒体一定会大做文章
Oh, man, the press is going to have a field day with this.

412
00:24:38,220 --> 00:24:40,560
这房间之外没有人知道这件事
No one outside of this room knows anything about it.

413
00:24:40,640 --> 00:24:41,510
会的
They will.

414
00:24:41,660 --> 00:24:42,930
他们总是有办法知道
They always do.

415
00:24:43,020 --> 00:24:44,190
媒体会找上门
It'll come out.

416
00:24:44,350 --> 00:24:45,810
你说得完全正确
You're absolutely right about that.

417
00:24:45,900 --> 00:24:47,940
不过到时候
But when it does,

418
00:24:48,020 --> 00:24:52,110
我们会说你和哈丁交情不深
we'll downplay your relationship with Hardin somehow.

419
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:56,990
- 怎样？ - 怎样？
- What? - What?

420
00:24:57,320 --> 00:24:58,660
回避问题
Defuse it.

421
00:24:59,240 --> 00:25:01,540
- 什么？你不同意吗？ - 不是
- What? You disagree? - No.

422
00:25:02,700 --> 00:25:04,620
其实，是的
Well, actually, yes.

423
00:25:04,710 --> 00:25:07,540
恕我直言，但我会反其道而行
Forgive me, but I would go in the other direction.

424
00:25:07,670 --> 00:25:09,880
要是记者问你和哈丁是不是朋友
If a reporter asked if you and Hardin were friends,

425
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:12,880
我会说“我们是好朋友”
I'd say, "No. We were good friends."

426
00:25:13,010 --> 00:25:14,800
要是问你们是不是好朋友
If they should ask if you were good friends,

427
00:25:14,880 --> 00:25:16,300
我会说“我们是一辈子好友”
I'd say, "No, no, we were lifelong friends."

428
00:25:16,380 --> 00:25:19,180
我不会给他们做文章的空间
I would give them no place to go,

429
00:25:20,760 --> 00:25:22,930
没什么好报导，没故事好编
nothing to report, no story.

430
00:25:25,560 --> 00:25:29,770
我意思是事情已经发生了…
I mean, it's no sense defusing a bomb after it's already...

431
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:33,780
…回避是没用的
It's already gone off.

432
00:25:57,930 --> 00:25:59,090
（加州，杭特利格特堡）
该死！可恶！
Damn. Shit!

433
00:26:01,600 --> 00:26:03,060
你看见他吗？
You see him?

434
00:26:04,270 --> 00:26:05,240
好吧
All right.

435
00:26:05,710 --> 00:26:07,640
小组往左移两公尺
Move your team two meters to the left.

436
00:26:11,560 --> 00:26:12,600
好了
That's it.

437
00:26:13,230 --> 00:26:14,020
停
Stop.

438
00:26:14,520 --> 00:26:16,190
摸摸浅色草堆
Touch that light-colored grass.

439
00:26:16,280 --> 00:26:18,070
狙击手在你脚下
Sniper at your feet.

440
00:26:20,110 --> 00:26:22,080
什么都没有，士官长
There's nothing here, Sergeant Major.

441
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:23,410
该死！
Damn!

442
00:26:23,490 --> 00:26:24,910
他真行
He is good.

443
00:26:41,930 --> 00:26:44,310
差一点，他怎么移动得这么快？
That was close. How's he moving so fast?

444
00:26:50,940 --> 00:26:53,190
我看到他了 直直往前
I see him. Come in. Straight in.

445
00:26:53,270 --> 00:26:54,650
快点！用跑的！
Now! Run!

446
00:26:56,480 --> 00:26:57,940
继续往前！
Keep coming.

447
00:27:00,030 --> 00:27:01,100
停
Stop.

448
00:27:01,320 --> 00:27:02,510
往左边
To your left,

449
00:27:03,020 --> 00:27:03,950
往左边
to your left.

450
00:27:05,620 --> 00:27:08,120
停，狙击手在你脚下
And stop. Sniper at your feet.

451
00:27:11,210 --> 00:27:12,830
不然是什么？
Well, what is it?

452
00:27:16,500 --> 00:27:19,130
他在这里吃午餐，士官长
He had lunch here, Sergeant Major.

453
00:27:19,220 --> 00:27:21,000
麦当劳汉堡 足三两
McDonald's. Quarter Pounder...

454
00:27:21,740 --> 00:27:22,680
加起司
with cheese.

455
00:27:24,640 --> 00:27:25,810
该死
Damn.

456
00:27:32,310 --> 00:27:34,060
- 该死！ - 第四枪了
- Damn! - That's four.

457
00:27:36,150 --> 00:27:37,940
好了，你赢了！
All right, you won this one!

458
00:27:38,030 --> 00:27:39,490
出来吧！
Come on out!

459
00:27:41,860 --> 00:27:44,950
士兵，你怎么能靠得这么近？
Soldier, how did you get that close to me?

460
00:27:45,030 --> 00:27:49,250
狙击手本来就是神出鬼没
Sniper approached the instructor by being a sneaky bastard,

461
00:27:49,330 --> 00:27:50,460
士官长！
Sergeant Major!

462
00:27:50,540 --> 00:27:52,290
知道在加州乱丢垃圾
Do you know the fine for littering

463
00:27:52,370 --> 00:27:54,790
要罚多少钱吗？
in the State of California, Chavez?

464
00:27:54,880 --> 00:27:56,210
知道，长官！
Yes, sir!

465
00:27:59,880 --> 00:28:03,050
我看到你在训练场的表现，你很行
I saw you on the sniper course. You looked good.

466
00:28:03,680 --> 00:28:06,050
这里的任务快完成了，对吧，中士？
Just about finished here, aren't you, Sergeant?

467
00:28:06,180 --> 00:28:07,310
对，长官
Yes, sir.

468
00:28:07,390 --> 00:28:11,230
期待放长假跟年轻妻子及孩子团聚？
Looking forward to taking some leave with that young wife and kids?

469
00:28:12,270 --> 00:28:14,940
我没有年轻妻子及孩子
I don't have any young wife and kids, sir.

470
00:28:15,020 --> 00:28:16,400
你有什么？
What do you have?

471
00:28:17,110 --> 00:28:20,780
你很少打电话
I mean, you don't call anybody with great frequency,

472
00:28:20,860 --> 00:28:23,530
信件往来也很少
don't write many letters, don't receive them.

473
00:28:26,410 --> 00:28:28,870
容我问一下，长官，你是谁？
Who are you, sir, if you don't mind my asking?

474
00:28:28,950 --> 00:28:31,160
克拉克先生和我共同负责一个特殊任务
Mr. Clark and I are putting together a special mission

475
00:28:31,250 --> 00:28:34,370
任务领导人要我的小组参与其中
and the group commander wants my team to be a part of it.

476
00:28:34,460 --> 00:28:36,170
为期大约六个月
You'd be gone a couple of months, maybe six,

477
00:28:36,250 --> 00:28:38,800
之后要是没死的话
after which, if you're not dead,

478
00:28:38,880 --> 00:28:41,880
你可以选择加入特种部队
you'd have your choice of assignments in Special Ops.

479
00:28:51,600 --> 00:28:53,810
总统先生，你有没有任何评论？
Mr. President, do you have a comment on...

480
00:28:53,890 --> 00:28:55,190
总统先生！
Mr. President!

481
00:28:58,060 --> 00:28:59,070
总统先生
Mr. President.

482
00:28:59,150 --> 00:29:00,690
显然回避问题
And that appears to be defusing an issue

483
00:29:00,780 --> 00:29:04,490
就会让问题愈滚愈大，成为另一个丑闻
that was snowballing into yet another scandal for this administration.

484
00:29:04,570 --> 00:29:06,200
纽约时报报导
The New York Times is reporting

485
00:29:06,280 --> 00:29:07,950
你和哈丁是好朋友
that you and Hardin were good friends.

486
00:29:08,030 --> 00:29:08,870
是不是真的？
Is that true?

487
00:29:08,970 --> 00:29:10,320
不，不仅如此
No, not quite.

488
00:29:10,420 --> 00:29:11,650
我们不仅是好朋友
We weren't good friends.

489
00:29:11,980 --> 00:29:13,540
还是一辈子的好朋友
We were lifelong friends.

490
00:29:13,620 --> 00:29:15,080
那是我说的
I said that.

491
00:29:15,960 --> 00:29:17,330
那是我说的
I said that.

492
00:29:19,420 --> 00:29:21,630
我叫他那么说的
I told him to say that.

493
00:29:21,750 --> 00:29:22,710
怎样？
What?

494
00:29:23,400 --> 00:29:24,420
我什么都没说
I didn't say anything.

495
00:29:25,260 --> 00:29:28,090
- 对，但你心里在想  - 不
- Yeah, but you're thinking something. - No.

496
00:29:29,300 --> 00:29:31,390
我只是被你今天刻意打扮
I was just distracted by how much trouble

497
00:29:31,470 --> 00:29:33,850
分了心而已
you were having with your ensemble today.

498
00:29:35,270 --> 00:29:38,020
- 你不必每天穿得…  - 快点，萨利，快点，走了
- Well, it's not every day... - Come on, Sally. Hurry up, we gotta go.

499
00:29:38,100 --> 00:29:40,110
一副值得信任的样子
you have to look trustworthy.

500
00:29:40,190 --> 00:29:42,860
- 谁跟谁说了什么，爸？  - 没什么
- Who told who to say what, Dad? - It's not important.

501
00:29:42,940 --> 00:29:45,070
- 我可以自己走  - 我知道你可以
- I can walk myself. - I know you can.

502
00:29:45,150 --> 00:29:47,950
- 总统吗？  - 是啊
- The President? - Yeah.

503
00:29:48,030 --> 00:29:50,990
妈妈说她赚的钱比总统还多
Mom says she makes more money than the President.

504
00:29:51,120 --> 00:29:52,860
拜，爸，再见
Bye, Dad. See you.

505
00:29:52,960 --> 00:29:54,540
她也许是对的，再见
She's probably right. Bye.

506
00:30:04,130 --> 00:30:06,300
莱恩博士，谢谢你今天下午
I want to thank you, Dr. Ryan, for the information

507
00:30:06,380 --> 00:30:08,680
跟我们分享了这些资讯
you've shared with us this afternoon.

508
00:30:09,470 --> 00:30:10,720
谢了，参议员
Thank you, Senator.

509
00:30:10,800 --> 00:30:12,930
我同意我们必须协助哥伦比亚
I agree we have to help the Colombians

510
00:30:13,010 --> 00:30:17,600
打击贩毒集团的活动
in their struggle to curtail the drug cartels' activities.

511
00:30:17,690 --> 00:30:20,020
然而我不明白
However, I'm confused.

512
00:30:22,060 --> 00:30:23,900
增加拨款如何让此计划
How do you see additional funds alone

513
00:30:23,980 --> 00:30:27,200
从失败中起死回生？
advancing this program from the utter failure that it is?

514
00:30:27,320 --> 00:30:29,240
明白我的意思吗？
You see what I'm getting at?

515
00:30:29,320 --> 00:30:31,240
我恐怕不明白
No, I'm afraid I don't.

516
00:30:31,870 --> 00:30:35,040
你刚说此计划我方完全采温和政策
You said this effort would be totally benign on our part.

517
00:30:35,160 --> 00:30:36,520
报告上说得很清楚
Well, the finding clearly states

518
00:30:36,600 --> 00:30:40,120
我方仅限于提供意见而已，参议员
that our assistance is limited to supply and advice only, Senator.

519
00:30:40,210 --> 00:30:41,960
我知道，我看过了
I know. I've read that.

520
00:30:42,040 --> 00:30:44,040
我这星期也看了
I've also read a similar finding,

521
00:30:44,130 --> 00:30:46,630
35年前的一份类似报告
written 35 years ago this week,

522
00:30:46,710 --> 00:30:50,800
关于在东南亚我们一无所悉的丛林
regarding a little-thought-of sliver of jungle in Southeast Asia.

523
00:30:50,890 --> 00:30:51,930
不好意思
I'm sorry.

524
00:30:52,010 --> 00:30:54,390
你拿我们的
You're comparing our request

525
00:30:54,510 --> 00:30:57,310
反毒行动补助款申请案跟越战相比拟？
for supplemental anti-drug funds to Vietnam?

526
00:30:57,450 --> 00:30:59,100
每次我都会这样比拟
I'm comparing it to every instance

527
00:30:59,170 --> 00:31:01,530
在这种立法机构每次要对
a legislative body such as this is asked to

528
00:31:01,660 --> 00:31:04,610
缺乏实证的案件做判断时
render judgment based on less than all the facts.

529
00:31:09,240 --> 00:31:12,070
我不知道该说什么了
Well, I'm afraid I don't know what to say to that.

530
00:31:12,200 --> 00:31:13,780
你可以跟我们保证
You could begin by assuring us

531
00:31:13,880 --> 00:31:15,370
所有事实都已呈报
we have been given all the facts.

532
00:31:15,450 --> 00:31:17,160
我想我是的
I thought I had.

533
00:31:17,250 --> 00:31:18,660
你还可以进一步保证
You could further assure us, then,

534
00:31:18,750 --> 00:31:20,240
这次增加的拨款
that this increase in funds,

535
00:31:20,300 --> 00:31:22,720
或你说的补助款
this "escalation," to use your word,

536
00:31:23,130 --> 00:31:26,130
将不会用在任何秘密的军事行动上
will not be used for any covert military action.

537
00:31:27,130 --> 00:31:30,220
我不知道你怎么会这么想
I don't know how you're getting to this.

538
00:31:30,550 --> 00:31:32,390
根据我丰富的经验
Long experience, sir.

539
00:31:34,140 --> 00:31:35,760
绝不派兵
No troops, then.

540
00:31:36,260 --> 00:31:40,560
我特别说清楚点，因为我不希望有任何误解
I enunciate that clearly because I don't want there to be any mistake.

541
00:31:41,940 --> 00:31:43,270
绝不派兵
No troops.

542
00:31:44,560 --> 00:31:46,940
你可以跟我保证吗？
You could say I have your word on that?

543
00:31:47,570 --> 00:31:50,070
可以，因为我说话算话
You could, indeed, because you do.

544
00:31:58,410 --> 00:32:01,960
- 数到三往下跳  - 好的

545
00:32:05,750 --> 00:32:07,130
听好！
Listen up!

546
00:32:07,630 --> 00:32:09,010
军籍牌！
Dog tags.

547
00:32:09,090 --> 00:32:10,320
全部拿下来
Take them off.

548
00:32:10,960 --> 00:32:12,260
往前传过来
Pass them forward.

549
00:32:12,800 --> 00:32:16,970
检查口袋有没有任何辨别身分的物件
Check your pockets for anything that can be used for identification.

550
00:32:26,110 --> 00:32:27,610
我们在陆地上空
We're feet dry.

551
00:32:41,540 --> 00:32:43,660
看到降落点，请准备
LZ in sight. Get ready.

552
00:32:44,710 --> 00:32:47,290
祝好运，去收拾他们吧！
Good luck, boys. Go get them.

553
00:32:51,380 --> 00:32:54,180
准备降落了
Okay, let's take her down now. We're going down.

554
00:33:10,190 --> 00:33:11,570
快！快！快！
Go! Go! Go!

555
00:34:06,370 --> 00:34:09,580
（后备队罗伯特·里特有内部讯息，连接？是的）

556
00:34:19,760 --> 00:34:24,770
（恭喜，詹姆斯，你的小小战争）

557
00:34:24,930 --> 00:34:27,600
（已经展开了）

558
00:34:40,910 --> 00:34:42,120
嘿，巴伯
Hey, Bob.

559
00:34:44,790 --> 00:34:46,830
- 你好吗？  - 很好，先生
- How you doing? - Good, sir.

560
00:34:48,250 --> 00:34:49,830
很高兴见到你
Good to see you.

561
00:34:56,130 --> 00:34:57,420
- 早安，杰克  - 早安
- Good morning, Jack. - Good morning.

562
00:34:57,510 --> 00:34:58,440
莱恩
Ryan,

563
00:34:58,900 --> 00:34:59,870
进来吧
come on in.

564
00:35:00,260 --> 00:35:01,180
认识大家吗？
You know everyone?

565
00:35:01,260 --> 00:35:02,720
认识、认识
Yes, yes.

566
00:35:02,800 --> 00:35:03,760
咖啡？面包？
Coffee, bagel?

567
00:35:03,960 --> 00:35:05,720
黑咖啡，谢谢
Coffee. Black, please.

568
00:35:05,810 --> 00:35:08,270
家人好吗？
So, how's the family?

569
00:35:08,980 --> 00:35:10,440
很好
Good, sir.

570
00:35:10,770 --> 00:35:12,980
何时可以见见莱恩医生？
When am I gonna meet the other Dr. Ryan?

